[1]
Date: Thu 19 Sep 2002
From: "Pablo Nart" <p.nart@virgin.net>
Source: The Daily Star Internet Edition, Thu 19 Sep 2002 [edited]
<http://www.dailystarnews.com/200209/19/n2091906.htm#BODY7>

Bangladesh: 43 More People Contract Dengue Fever
------------------------------------------------
Forty-three more people were admitted to different public and private
hospitals with dengue fever yesterday but none died during the period, a
Health Directorate Control Room source said.
A total of 4955 people has been attacked with dengue so far. Of these, 45
have died and 178 are undergoing treatment in different hospitals, the
source added. Twenty persons were admitted to Shaheed Suhrawardy Hospital,
4 to Mitford Hospital, 4 to Holy Family Hospital, 4 to Central Hospital, 3
to Dhaka Medical College Hospital, one to Sishu Hospital, one to Nibedita
Hospital, 4 to Khulna Medical College Hospital and one to Chittagong
MedicalCollege Hospital.

